    {
        "content": "<p>mattberther <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/153#issuecomment-361113269\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/153#issuecomment-361113269\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/153\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/153\">PR #153</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>@bakerdb The optional/required element as described in this PR are intended to be hook-specific. This should not be interpreted to imply that context must always include a patientId or encounterId. </p>\n<p>Can you think of a way we can make this clearer?</p>\n</blockquote>",
