    {
        "content": "<p>kpshek <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/153#issuecomment-361281093\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/153#issuecomment-361281093\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/153\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/cds-hooks/docs/pull/153\">PR #153</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>@kpshek It seems to me that \"patient\" should be OPTIONAL even when pulled within \"context.\" Looks like #153 makes \"encounter\" optional, but not \"patient.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>@bakerdb - For the three hooks we have defined today, <code>patientId</code> is REQUIRED for all of them. The reason is that for each of these hooks, you always have a patient in context. However, you may not have an encounter opened. This is actually have things have always worked previously with these hooks in CDS Hooks; we're just making that explicit here.</p>\n</blockquote>",
